dct_description_sm: The Warren Heckrotte Map Collection includes over 150 maps primarily of the American West.  The collection has a strong focus on maps from the California gold rush as well as early exploration of the American West including coastal exploration.  The maps range in date from 1734 to 1916.
dct_rights_sm: Images from the Warren Heckrotte Map Collection courtesy Stanford University Libraries. These items are in the public domain.  There are no restrictions on use.  If you have questions, please contact the David Rumsey Map Center at rumseymapcenter@stanford.edu.
